abstract: They are our apex predator, the deadliest hunters of human beings on the planet.
snippet: They are our apex predator, the deadliest hunters of human beings on the planet.
lead_paragraph: It has been one of the most aggravating sounds on earth for more than 100 million years — the humming buzz of a mosquito.

abstract: The 2020 Democrats reacted to the Mueller testimony, candidates tried out attacks before next week’s debates and Joe Biden received some good news.

abstract: The federal government has not executed anyone since 2003, but the attorney general announced that five inmates will be put to death starting in December.
snippet: The federal government has not executed anyone since 2003, but the attorney general announced that five inmates will be put to death starting in December.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The federal government will resume executions of death row inmates after a nearly two-decade hiatus, Attorney General William P. Barr said Thursday, countering a broad national shift away from the death penalty as public support for capital punishment has dwindled.

abstract: Tom Steyer plans to spend $100 million of his own money to take on President Trump, whether anyone wants him to or not.
snippet: Tom Steyer plans to spend $100 million of his own money to take on President Trump, whether anyone wants him to or not.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Tom Steyer is a former hedge fund investor and a billionaire. Those things could be a liability for a man running for president as a progressive. But Mr. Steyer, who this month joined a field of — what is it now? — 24 people, argued this was a selling point.

abstract: Eric Swalwell exits the race as Tom Steyer enters it, the candidates talk equity at the Essence Festival, and Joe Biden releases his tax returns.

abstract: You have no constituency other than yourself. There are plenty of better things for you to do with your money.
snippet: You have no constituency other than yourself. There are plenty of better things for you to do with your money.
lead_paragraph: I am pointedly trying not to make predictions about the presidential race. But I think I can say with confidence that Tom Steyer — a hedge fund billionaire who announced this week that he, too, was running for president — will not be the Democratic nominee.
